      • setGroupFilter

        public ALBLdapDirectorySettings.Builder setGroupFilter(java.lang.String groupFilter)
        Group filter is used to identify groups during search. Default value when not specified in API or module is interpreted by ALB Controller as (objectClass=(STAR)).
        Parameters:
        groupFilter - New value for the property.

      • setGroupMemberAttribute

        public ALBLdapDirectorySettings.Builder setGroupMemberAttribute(java.lang.String groupMemberAttribute)

        Parameters:
        groupMemberAttribute - New value for the property.

      • setGroupMemberIsFullDn

        public ALBLdapDirectorySettings.Builder setGroupMemberIsFullDn(java.lang.Boolean groupMemberIsFullDn)
        Group member entries contain full DNs instead of just user id attribute values. Default value when not specified in API or module is interpreted by ALB Controller as true.
        Parameters:
        groupMemberIsFullDn - New value for the property.

      • setGroupSearchDn

        public ALBLdapDirectorySettings.Builder setGroupSearchDn(java.lang.String groupSearchDn)
        LDAP group search DN is the root of search for a given group in the LDAP directory. Only matching groups present in this LDAP directory sub-tree will be checked for user membership.
        Parameters:
        groupSearchDn - New value for the property.

      • setGroupSearchScope

        public ALBLdapDirectorySettings.Builder setGroupSearchScope(java.lang.String groupSearchScope)
        Possible values are:
        • ALBLdapDirectorySettings.GROUP_SEARCH_SCOPE_BASE
        • ALBLdapDirectorySettings.GROUP_SEARCH_SCOPE_ONE
        • ALBLdapDirectorySettings.GROUP_SEARCH_SCOPE_SUBTREE
        LDAP group search scope defines how deep to search for the group starting from the group search DN. Enum options - AUTH_LDAP_SCOPE_BASE, AUTH_LDAP_SCOPE_ONE, AUTH_LDAP_SCOPE_SUBTREE. Default value when not specified in API or module is interpreted by ALB Controller as AUTH_LDAP_SCOPE_SUBTREE.
        Parameters:
        groupSearchScope - New value for the property.

      • setIgnoreReferrals

        public ALBLdapDirectorySettings.Builder setIgnoreReferrals(java.lang.Boolean ignoreReferrals)
        During user or group search, ignore searching referrals. Default value when not specified in API or module is interpreted by ALB Controller as false.
        Parameters:
        ignoreReferrals - New value for the property.

      • setUserSearchDn

        public ALBLdapDirectorySettings.Builder setUserSearchDn(java.lang.String userSearchDn)
        LDAP user search DN is the root of search for a given user in the LDAP directory. Only user records present in this LDAP directory sub-tree will be validated.
        Parameters:
        userSearchDn - New value for the property.

      • setUserSearchScope

        public ALBLdapDirectorySettings.Builder setUserSearchScope(java.lang.String userSearchScope)
        Possible values are:

        • ALBLdapDirectorySettings.USER_SEARCH_SCOPE_ONE
        • ALBLdapDirectorySettings.USER_SEARCH_SCOPE_SUBTREE
        LDAP user search scope defines how deep to search for the user starting from user search DN. Enum options - AUTH_LDAP_SCOPE_BASE, AUTH_LDAP_SCOPE_ONE, AUTH_LDAP_SCOPE_SUBTREE. Default value when not specified in API or module is interpreted by ALB Controller as AUTH_LDAP_SCOPE_ONE.
        Parameters:
